list.name: Default Changelist
list.comment: Altered comments error messages to suit scenarios where comments are disabled on a video. Also reverted settings activity to a prior point, since the theme was not changing consistently.

task.summary: Default task
Finished OAuth authentication and began prototyping the means by which the application will receive user subscription data.
Improved searchbar feature to match Material 2.0 Guidelines.
Added a navigation drawer to the action bar that abides by Material 2.0 Guidelines.
The ability to refresh feed is now implemented, with the setting of account details in the nav bar now in the works.
The ability to view video comments has now been implemented, with minor tweaks to the UI color also being a more recent add-on.
The app user may now view subscription videos that have been uploaded within the past 2 days on their main account.
Implemented Trending activity and began migrating app content to fragments.
Added view count summary to video CardView layout and implemented Joda-Time for the purpose of formatting video timestamps.
The MaterialSearchView widget is now capable of forwarding search queries to the search fragment, which can then replace the RecyclerView accordingly.
Moved the API key to its own class for ease of access, and added SharedPreferences to each fragment for the purpose of lowering the daily Google API consumption amount.
Moved the API key to its own class for ease of access, and added SharedPreferences to each fragment for the purpose of lowering the daily Google API consumption amount.
Added search suggestions to the SearchView and stylized the search bar using Material 2.0 guidelines.
Migrated SettingsFragment to SettingsActivity, and added the ability to clear history from SQLLite database using a preference click listener.

The ability to switch between Dark Theme and the default app theme is now available, though its introduction has left a bug in the SearchView feature since its operation interferes with the onResume function.

The ability to switch between Dark Theme and the default app theme is now available, though its introduction has left a bug in the SearchView feature since its operation interferes with the onResume function.
Fixed a bug that impacted the ability to switch between the app theme and dark theme.
Fixed a UI bug within the SettingsActivity that resulted from the merging of two styles.
Fixed a error where setImageFromResource within the search suggestions was causing the app to crash as a result of a null object reference.

Implemented SearchFragment in a way that allows for outbound queries from ProfileActivity to be retrieved and used within a Google API call. Known issue: the SearchActivity does not open when a query is submitted within the SearchView.
Fixed a UI bug that resulted in the bottom card within the RecyclerView being cut off.
Reverted the return back to true on the onQueryTextSubmit method since it prevented the SearchView from displaying search results.
Reverted Video.java onCreate to a previous state to enable VideoStats data to be accessed within the detail view of each video displayed using the Search:list endpoint.
Added the ability to search multiple times in succession, with the ability to delete existing activities by using onBackPressed().
Added animation to the SearchView feature, as well as the fragments located within the ProfileActivity. Several files have also been refactored to more accurately reflect their purpose.
Overhauled the color scheme of the application.
Refactored VideoDetails models to their own seperate folder.
Finished the migration of data request classes to AsyncTask for better performance on the UI thread.
Added the ability to view suggested videos based on the current video the user is on.
UI on the VideoActivity fragment was overhauled to suit the new recommendation functionality.
Updated ProfileActivity UI to more closely match the UI of the VideoActivity.
Added the ability to share videos to a source of the user's choice.
Made further changes to the VideoActivity UI for sake of optimization.
Fixed an issue where a lack of a searchable configuration within the SearchActivity manifest prevented search suggestions from being displayed.
Patched a minor UI bug that would result from an activity refresh in response to a theme change in the SettingsActivity.
Patched a minor UI bug that would result from an activity refresh in response to a theme change in the SettingsActivity.
Began Kotlin project conversion, starting with the helper classes of SharedPref, Animations, Credentials, SuggestionProvider, and TopGravityDrawable.
Optimized the view hierarchy for VideoActivity to enable faster load times.
Fixed inconsistencies with the current working version that would result in the theme not changing when the settings toggle was invoked.
Altered comments error messages to suit scenarios where comments are disabled on a video. Also reverted settings activity to a prior point, since the theme was not changing consistently.
